I agree with everyone about the advantages of XML; I was mainly just
trying to advocate a conversion utility for those of us left with
older versions of NEAT.  As people said, such a conversion wouldn&#39;t
be too difficult in either direction.  One reason it would be nice is
because for example I would like to run my old genome files through
Derek and Philip&#39;s visualization, since it looks nicer than what I
currently have working in Gtk.  

A few more comments on the genome format below...

