The connections gene representation seems to be missing two features
that I would expect it to have:

   -An enable/disable bit
   -A recurrency flag

In particular, I am not sure how the NEAT algorithm can be 
implemented (with respect to the standard operations in our papers)
without the ability to disable a gene?  Also the previous discussion
on simplification would require such a tag.

The recurrency flag isn&#39;t really necessary, but I have one in my
genome files because it&#39;s very convenient to sort of quickly get
a sense of how much recurrency is being used, and it is also 
convenient in some cases for graphing to know immediately which 
connections are recurrent so they can be treated differently.

One other thing about printing out entire populations.  In my
population files (which C++ NEAT users may have noticed are usually
called gen_#) I concatenate the whole population of genomes into
a single file, wherein the genomes are clustered by species, and
there is a comment line before each species and before each individual
